tasks.instruction:
1. Add chat API functions to forge-web/lib/api.ts:
   - chat.send(context, message, sessionId?, model?) -> {session_id}
   - chat.getSession(sessionId) -> {messages, tokens, cost}
   - chat.listSessions() -> {sessions}
   - chat.getProviders() -> {providers}
   - chat.testProvider(provider) -> {status, latency}
   - chat.getConfig() -> {feature_flags, permissions}
   - chat.updateConfig(config) -> updated
2. Create forge-web/stores/chatStore.ts:
   - State: conversations Map, activeSessionId, streaming, error
   - ChatConversation: sessionId, messages[], context, totalTokens, cost
   - ChatMessage: id, role, content, toolCalls?, toolResults?, streaming?
   - Actions: sendMessage, startConversation, addToken, addToolCall, completeMessage
   - WS handler for chat.* events
3. Add chat types to forge-web/lib/types.ts
4. Register chat WS events in wsDispatcher.ts
5. Add react-markdown and remark-gfm to package.json

1. In forge-web/app/globals.css: replace --sidebar-width: 240px with new variables:
   --topnav-height: 48px;
   --left-panel-width: 224px;
   --right-sidebar-width: 420px;
   --right-sidebar-collapsed-width: 40px;
2. In forge-web/app/layout.tsx: remove p-6 from <main> className. Change from 'flex-1 overflow-y-auto p-6' to 'flex-1 overflow-hidden' (overflow management moves to child layouts).
3. Update forge-web/tailwind.config.ts: add custom spacing tokens referencing the CSS variables if useful for Tailwind classes.
4. Verify the build compiles without errors after these foundational changes.
